                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "1e964425-4b7d-34ba-a00e-cfc1eca95c1c",
              "name": "Hardcoded Credential Stored in Package-Level Variable Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nHardcoded Credential Stored in Package-Level Variable Vulnerability in Go programming language refers to the insecure practice of embedding plaintext credentials directly into the source code. This vulnerability can lead to unauthorized access if the source code is ever exposed. The credentials could be for any service that the application interacts with such as databases, cloud services, or other external systems.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, the variable `CloudCredentialResourceName` is hardcoded with the value `\"cloudcredentials\"`. If this variable is used as a credential for accessing a cloud resource, it poses a security risk.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nAvoid hardcoding credentials in your source code. Instead, use environment variables, configuration files, or secure vaults to store sensitive information. These methods allow you to separate the credentials from the code and change them without the need for a new deployment.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of hardcoding the credentials, you can use environment variables. Here is how you can do it in Go:\n\n```go\nimport \"os\"\n\nvar CloudCredentialResourceName string\n\nfunc init() {\n    CloudCredentialResourceName = os.Getenv(\"CLOUD_CREDENTIAL_RESOURCE_NAME\")\n    if CloudCredentialResourceName == \"\" {\n        log.Fatal(\"missing environment variable CLOUD_CREDENTIAL_RESOURCE_NAME\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, the `CLOUD_CREDENTIAL_RESOURCE_NAME` environment variable is used to set the value of `CloudCredentialResourceName`. If the environment variable is not set, the program will log a fatal error and exit.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example does not require any external library dependencies.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP: Hardcoded Security Credentials](https://owasp.org/www-community/vulnerabilities/Use_of_hard-coded_password)\n- [CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-798",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-798"
                ]
              }
