            {
              "id": "2e47fad5-4c71-30e0-8ee8-f3c49e7bdd12",
              "name": "Hardcoded Credential Stored in Package-Level Variable",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Hardcoded Credential Stored in Package-Level Variable\" is a vulnerability that occurs when sensitive data such as credentials, cryptographic keys, or other secrets are hardcoded into the source code. In Go programming language, this vulnerability can occur when such sensitive data is stored in package-level variables. This is a security risk as it exposes the sensitive data to unauthorized access and potential misuse. If an attacker gains access to the source code, they can easily retrieve these hardcoded credentials and use them for malicious purposes.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nAvoid hardcoding sensitive data in your source code. Instead, use secure methods to store and retrieve these data, such as environment variables, secure configuration files, or secure vault services. \n\nEnsure that your source code is properly protected and access is restricted to authorized personnel only. Regularly review your source code for potential security vulnerabilities and fix them promptly.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of hardcoding the secret request resource name in a package-level variable, you can store it in an environment variable. Here is how you can do it in Go:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"os\"\n)\n\nvar SecretRequestResourceName string\n\nfunc init() {\n    SecretRequestResourceName = os.Getenv(\"SECRET_REQUEST_RESOURCE_NAME\")\n    if SecretRequestResourceName == \"\" {\n        log.Fatal(\"SECRET_REQUEST_RESOURCE_NAME not set\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, the `SECRET_REQUEST_RESOURCE_NAME` environment variable is used to store the secret request resource name. The `os.Getenv` function is used to retrieve the value of this environment variable. If the environment variable is not set, the program will log a fatal error and exit.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- The `os` package from the Go standard library for accessing environment variables.\n- The `log` package from the Go standard library for logging errors.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP: Hardcoded Secrets](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Password_Storage_Cheat_Sheet.html#hardcoded-secrets)\n- [CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-798",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
