            {
              "id": "bff57f80-aaab-3c44-ba4a-b0937d2c31cd",
              "name": "Sensitive Data Exposure through Hardcoded Credentials or API Keys",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nSensitive Data Exposure through Hardcoded Credentials or API Keys is a security vulnerability that occurs when sensitive data such as credentials, API keys, or other secrets are hardcoded into the source code. This is a common issue in many programming languages, including Go. \n\nHardcoding sensitive information in the source code is a bad practice because it exposes the data to anyone who has access to the source code. This could include other developers, version control systems, or even attackers if the source code is publicly accessible. \n\nIn the provided Go code snippet, the `AuthConfigConditionSecretsMigrated` variable is hardcoded with the value `\"SecretsMigrated\"`. If this value is a sensitive secret, it could be exposed to unauthorized users.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, avoid hardcoding sensitive data in the source code. Instead, use secure methods to store and retrieve sensitive data, such as environment variables, secure configuration files, or secret management systems.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of hardcoding the secret, you can use an environment variable to store it. Here's how you can do it in Go:\n\n```go\nimport \"os\"\n\nfunc main() {\n    AuthConfigConditionSecretsMigrated := os.Getenv(\"SECRETS_MIGRATED\")\n    condition.Cond = AuthConfigConditionSecretsMigrated\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, the `SECRETS_MIGRATED` environment variable is used to store the secret. The `os.Getenv` function retrieves the value of the environment variable.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet does not require any additional library dependencies to execute properly.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A3:2017-Sensitive Data Exposure](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A3_2017-Sensitive_Data_Exposure)\n- [CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html)"
              },
