            {
              "id": "dd639427-6799-3ae0-b128-5d54d2bc1de6",
              "name": "SQL Injection Vulnerability through Non-Constant Variable Concatenation",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"SQL Injection Vulnerability through Non-Constant Variable Concatenation\" is a security vulnerability that occurs when an application builds SQL statements directly from user input. The attacker can inject SQL commands into these statements, which will then be executed by the database. In Go programming language, this vulnerability can occur when using the `+` operator to concatenate SQL queries with user-supplied input.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, the `searchAttr` and `searchKey` variables are concatenated to form a SQL query. If an attacker can control the value of these variables, they can manipulate the SQL query to perform unauthorized actions.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should use parameterized queries or prepared statements instead of concatenating strings to form SQL queries. This ensures that user-supplied input is always treated as literal data, not part of the SQL command.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of concatenating the variables directly into the query, you should use a parameterized query. Here's how you can modify the provided code snippet:\n\n```go\nquery := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s*\", searchAttr, searchKey)\ngroupListCall.Query(query)\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet does not indicate any specific library dependencies. However, to execute SQL queries in Go, you typically need the `database/sql` package and a driver for your specific database system.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP SQL Injection Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/SQL_Injection_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-89",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-89"
                ]
              }
