            {
              "id": "feedfc63-3249-38a2-9b22-e0b1ca993080",
              "name": "Hardcoded Credential Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nHardcoded Credential Vulnerability refers to the practice of embedding plaintext credentials directly into the source code. This vulnerability can lead to unauthorized access if the source code is exposed or if the credentials are not properly secured. In Go programming language, this vulnerability can occur if sensitive data such as passwords, API keys, or other secrets are hardcoded directly into the source code.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nAvoid hardcoding credentials directly into the source code. Instead, use environment variables, configuration files, or secure vaults to store sensitive data. Ensure that these storage methods are properly secured to prevent unauthorized access.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of hardcoding the condition directly into the source code, consider using a configuration file or environment variable to store the condition. Here is an example of how you can use an environment variable to store the condition:\n\n```go\nimport \"os\"\n\nfunc main() {\n    condition.Cond = os.Getenv(\"ACI_SECRETS_MIGRATED\")\n}\n```\n\nIn this example, the condition is stored in the `ACI_SECRETS_MIGRATED` environment variable. This prevents the condition from being hardcoded directly into the source code.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example does not appear to require any specific library dependencies.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 2017: A2-Broken Authentication](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A2_2017-Broken_Authentication)\n- [OWASP Cheat Sheet: Password Storage](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Password_Storage_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-798",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-798"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
